sentences: Marina Sergeevna Lizorkina (Russian: Марина Серге́евна Лизоркина; born 9 June 1983) is a Russian singer and former member of girl group Serebro which she left in 2009.
Marina Sergeevna Lizorkina (Russian: Марина Серге́евна Лизоркина; born 9 June 1983) is a Russian singer and former member of girl group Serebro which she left in 2009.
In 2004, they released a few singles for the series Obrechonnaya Stat Zvezdoy.
With Serebro, Lizorkina took part in the Eurovision Song Contest 2007 and placed the third.
They also released four No. 1 hits in Russia and the album Opiumroz in 2009.
On 18 June 2009, it was announced that Marina Lizorkina had left the band, for both financial and personal reasons, and was replaced by Anastasia Karpova.
She is also a fan of football and once stated that she was very happy because Russia played in the semi-finals of UEFA Euro 2008.
For this moment she exhibits in Russia, Europe and the United States
